            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Here lies Bassos the doctor. He lived for 50 years, and died 15 days before the Kalends of March.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#martaf">
                <p>Qui giace Bassos il medico. Visse 50 anni e mor&#236; 15 giorni prima delle Calende di marzo.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#martaf">
                <p>The epitaph presents the traditional expression <foreign xml:lang="grc">&#7952;&#957;&#952;&#940;&#948;&#949; &#954;&#949;&#8150;&#964;&#945;&#953;</foreign> (for the phonetic development of <foreign xml:lang="grc">&#954;&#949;&#8150;&#964;&#945;&#953;</foreign> into <foreign xml:lang="grc">&#954;&#949;&#8150;&#964;&#949;</foreign> from the 3rd cent. AD, see in Catania IG 14.532 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001351">ISic001351</ref>, Libertini (1930) 44 no.7 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001629">ISic001629</ref>), followed by the name of the deceased, the age and the date of death (in this case expressed with the verb <foreign xml:lang="grc">&#964;&#949;&#955;&#949;&#965;&#964;&#940;&#969;</foreign> in the aorist form), which is frequent in Christian epitaphs. In this case, there is the mention (rare in Christian epitaphs) of the profession of the deceased, <foreign xml:lang="grc">&#7984;&#945;&#964;&#961;&#972;&#962;</foreign>. For other Sicilian inscriptions mentioning doctors, see Rizzo, F. P. (1989), "La menzione del lavoro nelle epigrafi della Sicilia antica: Per una storia della mentalit&#224;", pp.62-64 and Manganaro, G. (1994), "Iscrizioni, epigrafi ed epigrammi in Greco della Sicilia orientale di epoca romana", in "M&#233;langes de l&#8217;&#201;cole Francaise de Rome: Antiquit&#233;" 106(1), 79&#8211;118, at p.107.</p>
            </div>
